      • setInputHandler

        public void setInputHandler(BiFunction<Interaction,String,String> inputHandler)
        Sets input handler. When input changes this handler will be called with the new input and should output what the text input should actually be set to. Return the input value if you only want to listen to changes.
        Parameters:
        inputHandler - the input handler
